The paper deals with the problem of determining the distance of a given graph to a sparse graph class, which is a topic in graph theory and combinatorics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also uses techniques from parameterized complexity, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper mentions minor-closed classes, which are a topic in graph theory and could place it in cs.GT (Graph Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the use of first-order definability, which is a topic in logic and could place it in cs.LG (Logic in Computer Science).
